"High on You" was Survivor's second hit single from their 1984 album Vital Signs. The song peaked at #8 in April 1985 on the Billboard Hot 100 chart.

Vital Signs is the fifth studio album by the American rock band Survivor and their first with vocalist Jimi Jamison. The album was a success in the U.S. where it hit #16 on the Billboard Album charts.

The album had three hit singles: "The Search Is Over" (#4 US), "High on You" (#8 US) and "I Can't Hold Back" (#13 US). "First Night", the fourth and final single from the album, peaked at #53 on the Billboard Hot 100 in September 1985.

Survivor is an American rock band formed in 1978. The band achieved its greatest success in the 1980s with its pop-rock sound, which garnered many charting singles, especially in the United States. The band is best known for its Double Platinum-certified 1982 mega-hit "Eye Of The Tiger", the theme song for the motion picture Rocky III (US #1 for 6 weeks). Singles like "Burning Heart" (US #2), "The Search Is Over" (#4 US), "High on You" (#8 US) and "I Can't Hold Back (US #13) continued to chart in the mid-1980s.
